.TH "GITPKG" "8" "" "gitpkg" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
gitpkg \[em] minimal package manager for git + make projects
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]gitpkg\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]args\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]gitpkg\f[R] is a repo\-agnostic package manager that clones git
repositories, builds and installs their contents with \f[B]make\f[R](1),
and tracks installed files.
Build and install steps run inside a \f[B]bubblewrap\f[R](1) sandbox
with PID, UTS, and IPC namespaces isolated and system directories
read\-only.
.PP
Packages can be installed by name (resolved from configured source URLs)
or by providing a direct git URL.
When installing by name, \f[B]gitpkg\f[R] constructs clone URLs from
each configured source as \f[I]base_url/package_name\f[R] and tries them
in order.
If the standalone repo is not found, it searches configured collection
repositories (a single git repo containing multiple packages as
subdirectories).
.PP
Before installation, the Makefile is displayed for review.
If \f[I]/etc/gitpkg/allowed_signers\f[R] or \f[I]signers.conf\f[R]
contains SSH public keys, \f[B]gitpkg\f[R] requires valid commit
signatures for install and update.
.PP
Packages installed by direct URL remember their source and update from
the same URL.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]install\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] <\f[I]name\f[R]|\f[I]url\f[R]> [\f[I]name\f[R]|\f[I]url\f[R]\&...]
Clone, build, and install one or more packages.
Accepts package names (resolved from configured sources) or direct git
URLs (\f[I]https://\f[R], \f[I]http://\f[R], \f[I]ssh://\f[R],
\f[I]git://\f[R], \f[I]git\[at]\f[R], \f[I]file://\f[R]).
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]update\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]name\f[R]\&...]
Update one or more packages to the latest commit.
When called without arguments, updates all installed packages.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]remove\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] <\f[I]name\f[R]> [\f[I]name\f[R]\&...]
Uninstall and remove source for one or more packages.
Each package is confirmed individually unless \f[B]\-y\f[R] is given.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]list\f[R]
List installed packages with their commit hashes and collection markers.
.TP
\f[B]status\f[R]
Check each installed package for upstream updates.
Uses \f[B]git ls\-remote\f[R](1) to compare local and remote HEAD
commits.
.TP
\f[B]files\f[R] <\f[I]name\f[R]>
List files tracked by an installed package.
.TP
\f[B]inspect\f[R] <\f[I]name\f[R]> [\f[I]url\f[R]]
Display the Makefile of a package before installing.
Can fetch from a remote URL, cached source, or collection.
.TP
\f[B]verify\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]fix\f[R]] [\f[I]name\f[R]]
Without arguments, verify system directory permissions.
When a package \f[I]name\f[R] is given, verify its checksums and file
integrity.
.TP
\f[B]search\f[R] <\f[I]query\f[R]>
Search known packages (from \f[I]pkglist\f[R]) and cached collections.
.TP
\f[B]repo\-add\f[R] <\f[I]base_url\f[R]>
Add a package source URL.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]repo\-del\f[R] <\f[I]base_url\f[R]>
Remove a package source URL.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]repo\-list\f[R]
List configured package sources (user repos and default mirrorlist).
.TP
\f[B]collection\-add\f[R] <\f[I]name\f[R]>
Register a collection repository.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]collection\-del\f[R] <\f[I]name\f[R]>
Unregister a collection repository.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]collection\-list\f[R]
List configured collections (user and default).
.TP
\f[B]signer\-add\f[R] <\f[I]principal\f[R]> <\f[I]ssh\-pubkey\f[R]>
Add a trusted SSH signing key.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]signer\-del\f[R] <\f[I]principal\f[R]>
Remove a trusted SSH signing key.
Requires root.
.TP
\f[B]signer\-list\f[R]
List trusted SSH signing keys (user and default keyring).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-n\f[R], \f[B]\[en]dry\-run\f[R]
Show what would be done without making changes.
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R], \f[B]update\f[R], and \f[B]remove\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-y\f[R], \f[B]\[en]yes\f[R]
Skip confirmation prompts.
Applies to \f[B]remove\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]skip\-inspect\f[R]
Skip Makefile review and confirmation.
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R] and \f[B]update\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]needed\f[R]
Do not reinstall packages that are already installed.
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]nodeps\f[R]
Skip dependency checks.
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R], \f[B]update\f[R], and \f[B]remove\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]nosig\f[R]
Skip commit signature verification.
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R] and \f[B]update\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]fix\f[R]
Auto\-repair permission anomalies found by \f[B]verify\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]clone\-timeout\f[R] <\f[I]seconds\f[R]>
Clone timeout in seconds (default: 120).
Overrides \f[I]CLONE_TIMEOUT\f[R] from \f[B]gitpkg.conf\f[R](5).
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R] and \f[B]update\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]fetch\-timeout\f[R] <\f[I]seconds\f[R]>
Fetch timeout in seconds (default: 30).
Overrides \f[I]FETCH_TIMEOUT\f[R] from \f[B]gitpkg.conf\f[R](5).
Applies to \f[B]install\f[R] and \f[B]update\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\[en]status\-timeout\f[R] <\f[I]seconds\f[R]>
Status check timeout in seconds (default: 15).
Overrides \f[I]STATUS_TIMEOUT\f[R] from \f[B]gitpkg.conf\f[R](5).
Applies to \f[B]status\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]\-h\f[R], \f[B]\[en]help\f[R]
Show usage summary and exit.
.TP
\f[B]\-V\f[R], \f[B]\[en]version\f[R]
Show version and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
\f[B]gitpkg\f[R] can be configured via
\f[I]/etc/gitpkg/gitpkg.conf\f[R].
Values set in the config file can be overridden by command\-line flags.
The file format is \f[I]KEY=VALUE\f[R], one per line.
Lines starting with \f[B]#\f[R] are ignored.
.TP
\f[B]CLONE_TIMEOUT\f[R]
Timeout in seconds for \f[B]git clone\f[R] operations.
Default: \f[B]120\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]FETCH_TIMEOUT\f[R]
Timeout in seconds for \f[B]git fetch\f[R] operations.
Default: \f[B]30\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]STATUS_TIMEOUT\f[R]
Timeout in seconds for \f[B]git ls\-remote\f[R] status checks.
Default: \f[B]15\f[R].
.SH SIGNATURE VERIFICATION
If \f[I]/etc/gitpkg/allowed_signers\f[R] or
\f[I]/etc/gitpkg/signers.conf\f[R] contains SSH public keys,
\f[B]gitpkg\f[R] requires valid commit signatures for install and update
operations.
Unsigned or untrusted commits are rejected.
.PP
Default keys ship in \f[I]/etc/gitpkg/allowed_signers\f[R].
User keys are managed with the \f[B]signer\-add\f[R] and
\f[B]signer\-del\f[R] commands.
.PP
Use \f[B]\[en]nosig\f[R] to bypass signature verification.
.SH COLLECTIONS
A collection is a single git repository containing multiple packages as
subdirectories, each with its own Makefile:
.IP
.EX
packages/
├── foo/
│   └── Makefile
├── bar/
│   └── Makefile
└── baz/
    └── Makefile
.EE
.PP
When installing a package, \f[B]gitpkg\f[R] first tries standalone
repos, then searches all configured collections.
Default collections are listed in \f[I]/etc/gitpkg/collections\f[R].
User collections are managed with the \f[B]collection\-add\f[R] and
\f[B]collection\-del\f[R] commands.
.PP
During updates, \f[B]gitpkg\f[R] detects whether only the package\[cq]s
subdirectory changed within the collection and skips rebuilds when
unnecessary.
.SH DEPENDENCY CHECK
Packages may include a \f[I]depends\f[R] file listing dependencies:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]gitpkg\f[R]:\f[I]name\f[R] \[em] checked via
\f[I]/var/lib/gitpkg//\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]system\f[R]:\f[I]name\f[R] \[em] checked via \f[B]command
\-v\f[R](1) or \f[B]pacman \-Qq\f[R]
.PP
Use \f[B]\[en]nodeps\f[R] to skip the dependency check.
.SH BACKUP FILES
Packages may include a \f[I]backup\f[R] file listing configuration paths
that should be preserved on removal and handled carefully on update.
Paths are relative without leading \f[B]/\f[R].
.PP
